comment.author: 31181870@N05
comment._content: If the caption is correct then this photograph was probably taken by the late great Frank Hurley during Sir Douglas Mawsons first expedition to Cape Denison from 1911-1914.  Later expeditions used East Greenland Huskies so there is also a possibility that these are of the same breed.  They were considered to be the ideal sledging dog in Antarctica as they were larger and stronger  than the "popular" breeds of today, and were more suitable for hauling heavy loads.  I cannot see the sled and assume that is would be a Nanson type, these sleds could carry half a ton of equipment and were held together with rawhide (no nails or screws) and this allowed them to flex as they were pulled over uneven surfaces.  The dogs are in what is called a "Fan" trace.  Someone else may have more info.  Cheers
